title: Clavicular breaks silence after felony forgery and drug charges dropped in Arizona State University arrest case
summary_full: Braden “Clavicular” had his felony charges dropped on February 11, 2026, after being arrested near Arizona State University for allegedly using a fake ID. The Maricopa County Attorney said there was no reasonable likelihood of conviction, according to Joseph Bernstein of The New York Times. Clavicular reacted online and said he spent $100,000 on lawyers.
